"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/Disadvantage of immunotherapy is tumours lose their antigens frequently leading to the cells becoming nonstimulatory..md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/Disadvantage of immunotherapy is tumours lose their antigens frequently leading to the cells becoming nonstimulatory..md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/Disadvantage of immunotherapy is tumours lose their antigens frequently leading to the cells becoming nonstimulatory..md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Disadvantage of immunotherapy is tumours lose their antigens frequently leading to the cells becoming nonstimulatory..md#Disadvantage of immunotherapy is tumours lose their antigens frequently leading to the cells becoming non-stimulatory. However, the [[Loss of the IL4 cytokine is highly unlikely on tumour tissue as it would be self-effacing for the tumour to no longer express it.]] This makes the IL4 exodomain an interesting antigen for CAR-T cell therapy. [[Fusing the IL4 exodomain with the IL7 receptor endodomain, you can target tumour cells expressing the former receptor but stimulating a homeostatic environment with the latter.]]{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Disadvantage of immunotherapy is tumours lose their antigens frequently leading to the cells becoming nonstimulatory..md#References":true},"mtime":1709479458452,"size":647,"hash":"dc251af2633c27a1d4a93ce338456a5355f34c0e897e422da4e877c35751e600"}],"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.00856998,0.00454147,-0.02149635,0.04055354,0.05631776,-0.00075307,0.01918741,-0.03367852,-0.00569357,0.00513466,-0.0120327,-0.01057606,-0.03469771,-0.04803215,0.03043804,0.0056609,0.02944371,-0.02620737,-0.01073331,-0.00573975,0.03326393,-0.01372585,-0.01004292,0.02392101,-0.05505589,-0.02464848,0.01090995,0.00589401,-0.07182418,-0.06921681,0.00414917,0.01264968,0.0498355,0.01567831,0.01841752,0.00176831,0.01843767,-0.01492487,0.01098458,-0.02923647,-0.03022197,0.00606896,0.00381438,0.00543514,0.02173753,0.0463